# Security Guardrails

- Validate all external inputs at route boundaries.
- Do not log full request bodies containing sensitive fields.
- Return safe error messages to clients; avoid leaking stack internals.
- Protect all non-public endpoints with auth middleware.
- Use short-lived JWTs and server-side verification for Google tokens.
- Parameterize queries and keep ORM usage typed.
